# Pros 
# 1. Can help with any backups of any kind of code.
# 2. Restoring previous version of code.
# 3. Helps with collaboration. 
# 4. Makes code management more easy.

# Cons
# 1. Losing data.
# 2. Can create conflicts in code.
# 3. Exposing senstive data.
# 4. Not following conventions like documenting your code and commits
